<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  Validibot test fixture: a Peppol BIS Billing 3.0 (UBL) invoice that is
  WELL-FORMED and would pass UBL XSD structural validation, but FAILS a
  business rule that only Schematron can express.

  SEEDED DEFECT: TaxInclusiveAmount (120.00) != TaxExclusiveAmount (100.00)
  + TaxAmount (21.00). This trips rule VB-CO-15 in peppol_billing_subset.sch
  (the fixture analogue of EN 16931 BR-CO-15). An XSD cannot catch this,
  because the arithmetic relationship between three separate elements is not
  expressible in a grammar. This is exactly why the SchematronValidator exists.
-->
